---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const lastUpdated = '2026-05-25';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Service — Wyreup"
  description="The terms that govern your use of Wyreup, including free tools, the PRO tier, and credits."
>
  <article class="legal">
    <header>
      <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
      <p class="meta">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
    </header>

    <p class="lede">
      Plain summary: Wyreup provides access to freely available file
      utilities, organized for convenience. <strong>You use them.</strong>
      You choose the inputs, build the chains, run the tools, and decide
      what to do with the outputs. Wyreup is the access layer, not the
      author of what you build with it.
    </p>

    <h2>1. Who we are</h2>
    <p>
      "Wyreup," "we," "us," and "our" refer to <strong>Wyreup</strong>,
      operated from Indiana, United States. We publish the website
      wyreup.com and the <code>@wyreup/core</code>, <code>@wyreup/cli</code>,
      and <code>@wyreup/mcp</code> packages on npm. You can reach us at
      <strong>hello@wyreup.com</strong>.
    </p>

    <h2>2. What Wyreup is — and what it isn't</h2>
    <p>
      Wyreup provides access to a collection of independent file and
      text utilities. Most of the underlying capabilities (image
      compression, PDF extraction, regex generation, etc.) are
      commonly available on their own; we organize them behind a
      consistent interface, an optional chain runner, and an optional
      hosted-AI tier. The convenience of access does not make us the
      author of the work you do with the tools, the compositions you
      assemble, or the outputs you generate.
    </p>
    <p>There are two tiers:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Free tools</strong> run entirely on your device — in
        your browser, or locally via the CLI / MCP. Wyreup is not
        involved at runtime; your input files, parameters, and outputs
        never reach our infrastructure. Free tools require no account.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>PRO tools</strong> are tools where, when <strong>you</strong>
        invoke them, <strong>your</strong> input is forwarded through
        Wyreup's edge to a third-party hosted-AI model (Cloudflare
        Workers AI, or an external image-model provider) that
        <strong>you</strong> have selected by choosing the PRO tool.
        The model — not Wyreup — runs against your input. Wyreup is
        the conduit between you and the model; we route the request,
        bill the credit, and return the model's response to you. PRO
        usage requires an account and consumes credits.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      <strong>Wyreup is not</strong>:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        a storage service — we don't retain your files, your outputs, or
        the contents of anything you process;
      </li>
      <li>
        a professional-advice service — outputs from AI tools are not
        legal, medical, financial, accounting, engineering, or other
        professional advice, regardless of how authoritative they read;
      </li>
      <li>
        a notarization, signing, certification, or chain-of-custody
        service — outputs we produce have no legal weight unless you
        separately certify them;
      </li>
      <li>
        a guarantee of correctness — every tool may be wrong, incomplete,
        or unsuitable for your specific use case, and you are responsible
        for verifying outputs before relying on them.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. Accounts and API keys</h2>
    <p>
      An account is identified by an email and one or more API keys. We
      store the SHA-256 hash of each key — never the raw value. Treat
      your keys like passwords. You can revoke or rotate them at any
      time from your account page.
    </p>
    <p>
      You are responsible for activity originating from your keys. If
      you believe a key has been compromised, revoke it immediately at
      <a href="/account">wyreup.com/account</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>4. Credits</h2>
    <p>
      Credits are a prepaid unit that fund PRO tool runs. Pricing and
      the credit cost per tool are listed on
      <a href="/pro">our pricing page</a>. Credits do not expire, do not
      transfer between accounts, and have no cash value outside Wyreup.
      See <a href="/legal/refund">our refund policy</a> for refunds.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Your inputs, your chains, your outputs</h2>
    <p>
      You — not Wyreup — use the tools. You select which tools to run,
      you provide the inputs, you configure any chains or trigger rules,
      and you decide what to do with the outputs. Wyreup provides access
      to the tools and (for PRO) routes your input to the third-party
      model you've selected; we don't review, vouch for, or take
      responsibility for what you do with that access. You are solely
      responsible for:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Inputs.</strong> Every file, text, URL, or parameter you
        submit. You confirm you have the right to process it under
        applicable copyright, privacy, contractual, and other laws.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Chains and trigger rules.</strong> Compositions you build
        from individual tools — including any combination that, by virtue
        of being composed, produces a result with greater impact than
        any single step. Composing legal individual operations into an
        illegal aggregate operation is your responsibility, not ours.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Every action you take.</strong> Wyreup does not select
        files, choose tools, build chains, or fire actions on your
        behalf. <strong>You</strong> drop the file. <strong>You</strong>
        click the button. <strong>You</strong> save the trigger rule
        and choose to confirm it when a matching file arrives. Even
        when a configured trigger rule appears to act automatically,
        the rule itself is something you previously authored and
        confirmed; each match still surfaces a preview that requires
        your action to proceed unless you have explicitly marked the
        rule as trusted. Wyreup never initiates work against your data
        of its own accord. If you experience an outcome you didn't
        intend, the cause is your input, your tool choice, your chain,
        your trigger configuration, or your downstream use — not an
        action Wyreup took independently.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Outputs.</strong> Anything you generate using Wyreup —
        text, images, transcripts, summaries, redactions, extracted data,
        derivative files. We do not review outputs. We make no claim
        that an output is suitable for any purpose, including the
        specific purpose you generated it for.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Downstream use.</strong> What you do with outputs —
        publishing, sharing, sending, signing, relying on, building on
        top of — is entirely yours. Outputs are not Wyreup statements,
        positions, or endorsements.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>6. Acceptable use</h2>
    <p>You agree not to use Wyreup to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        process content you don't have the right to process, including
        copyrighted material without license, personal data of third
        parties without their consent, or trade secrets you don't have
        authority over;
      </li>
      <li>
        attempt to extract model weights, reverse-engineer hosted
        endpoints, or otherwise abuse the PRO infrastructure;
      </li>
      <li>
        circumvent the rate limits, credit checks, API authentication,
        webhook signatures, or any other technical control of our
        service;
      </li>
      <li>
        produce material that is illegal under the laws of the United
        States or the State of Indiana — including but not limited to
        child sexual abuse material (CSAM), content that incites
        imminent violence, malware, or material that violates
        intellectual-property law;
      </li>
      <li>
        impersonate any person or entity, including Wyreup or its
        employees, in outputs or in communications about Wyreup;
      </li>
      <li>
        use Wyreup to build a competing service that resells our PRO
        infrastructure under a different brand.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      We may suspend or revoke access for violation of these rules
      without refund of unused credits associated with the violating
      activity. We may also report unlawful activity to the appropriate
      authorities, and you waive any objection to that disclosure for
      activity that violates this section.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Disclaimer of warranties</h2>
    <p>
      Wyreup is provided <strong>"as is" and "as available."</strong> To
      the maximum extent permitted by law, we disclaim all warranties,
      whether express, implied, statutory, or otherwise — including
      warranties of merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose,
      non-infringement, title, accuracy, and any warranty arising from
      course of dealing, course of performance, or usage of trade.
    </p>
    <p>
      We do not warrant that Wyreup will be uninterrupted, error-free,
      secure, or free of harmful components, or that defects will be
      corrected. We do not warrant that any tool — free or PRO — will
      produce output that is accurate, complete, current, lawful, or
      suitable for your purpose. AI-generated output in particular may
      be wrong, misleading, biased, or fabricated; verify everything
      before relying on it.
    </p>
    <p>
      You are responsible for keeping your own backups of any data you
      process through Wyreup. We retain nothing.
    </p>
    <p>
      Some jurisdictions do not allow the exclusion of certain
      warranties. In those jurisdictions, the disclaimers above apply
      only to the extent permitted by law, and you may have additional
      rights as a consumer.
    </p>

    <h2>8. Limitation of liability</h2>
    <p>
      To the maximum extent permitted by law, our aggregate liability
      for any and all claims arising out of or related to your use of
      Wyreup — whether in contract, tort (including negligence), strict
      liability, statute, or any other theory — is limited to the
      greater of (a) the total amount you have paid us in the
      <strong>twelve months</strong> preceding the event giving rise to
      the claim, or (b) <strong>US $50</strong>.
    </p>
    <p>
      We are not liable for any <strong>indirect, incidental,
      consequential, special, exemplary, or punitive damages</strong> —
      including but not limited to lost profits, lost revenue, lost data,
      lost goodwill, business interruption, regulatory fines, or the
      cost of substitute services — even if we have been advised of the
      possibility of such damages and even if any remedy in these terms
      fails of its essential purpose.
    </p>
    <p>
      You acknowledge that the pricing of Wyreup, including the free
      tier and the small per-credit cost of the PRO tier, reflects this
      allocation of risk between us, and that the limits above are an
      essential basis of our agreement. They survive any termination of
      these terms or your use of Wyreup.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Carve-outs.</strong> Nothing in this section limits
      liability that cannot be limited by applicable law — including
      liability for fraud, fraudulent misrepresentation, gross
      negligence, willful misconduct, or death or personal injury caused
      by negligence. Nothing in this section affects your statutory
      rights as a consumer where those rights cannot be waived under the
      law of your jurisdiction. If any part of this section is held
      unenforceable, the rest remains in effect, and the unenforceable
      part will be limited to the maximum extent permitted by law.
    </p>

    <h2>9. Indemnification</h2>
    <p>
      You agree to defend, indemnify, and hold harmless Wyreup, its
      operators, employees, agents, and contractors from any claim,
      demand, loss, liability, damage, cost, or expense (including
      reasonable attorneys' fees) arising out of or related to:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>your use of Wyreup in violation of these terms or applicable law;</li>
      <li>
        content you submit, process, or produce through Wyreup — including
        claims that you didn't have the right to process the input or that
        the output infringes a third party's rights;
      </li>
      <li>
        chains or trigger rules you configure — including compositions
        that produce results with effects you did not anticipate;
      </li>
      <li>
        downstream use of any output, including publication, distribution,
        or reliance by you or anyone you share an output with.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      We may, at our option and at your expense, assume exclusive
      defense and control of any matter you would otherwise indemnify.
      You will cooperate with our defense and will not settle any matter
      without our prior written consent.
    </p>

    <h2>10. Force majeure</h2>
    <p>
      We are not liable for any failure or delay in performance caused
      by events beyond our reasonable control — including infrastructure
      outages (such as Cloudflare, npm, payment processors, or upstream
      AI providers), labor disputes, acts of government, network
      disruptions, cyberattacks targeting third parties, natural
      disasters, pandemics, or war. The affected obligation is suspended
      until the event ends; if the event continues for more than 30
      days, either party may terminate the affected service without
      further liability.
    </p>

    <h2>11. Subprocessors</h2>
    <p>For PRO usage we route your inputs through:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Cloudflare</strong> — hosting, edge compute (Pages Functions), database (D1), and AI inference (Workers AI).</li>
      <li><strong>An external image-model provider</strong> — hosts image PRO tools (background removal, upscaling). Current vendor disclosed on request.</li>
      <li><strong>Lemon Squeezy</strong> — merchant of record for credit purchases; receives your billing info, not your tool inputs.</li>
      <li><strong>Zoho (ZeptoMail)</strong> — transactional email delivery (welcome key, account notices).</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      See <a href="/legal/privacy">our privacy policy</a> for what each
      subprocessor receives.
    </p>

    <h2>12. Changes</h2>
    <p>
      We may update these terms. Material changes will be noted by
      updating the "Last updated" date and, where appropriate, by
      sending an email to your account address. Continued use of
      Wyreup after a change constitutes acceptance. If you do not
      accept a change, your remedy is to stop using Wyreup and request a
      refund per the refund policy.
    </p>

    <h2>13. Termination</h2>
    <p>
      You may close your account at any time by emailing
      <strong>hello@wyreup.com</strong>. Unused credits at the time of
      closure are refundable per the
      <a href="/legal/refund">refund policy</a>. We may suspend or
      terminate your access immediately if you violate section 6, with
      no refund for credits associated with the violating activity.
    </p>
    <p>
      Sections 5 (your inputs), 7 (warranty disclaimer), 8 (limitation
      of liability), 9 (indemnification), 14 (governing law), and any
      payment obligations you owe us survive termination.
    </p>

    <h2>14. Governing law and disputes</h2>
    <p>
      These terms are governed by the laws of the State of Indiana and
      the United States, without regard to conflict-of-law provisions.
      Disputes are subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the state
      and federal courts located in Indiana. You consent to personal
      jurisdiction there and waive any objection to venue.
    </p>
    <p>
      Any claim arising out of or relating to these terms or your use
      of Wyreup must be brought within <strong>one (1) year</strong>
      after the cause of action arose, or it is permanently barred,
      except to the extent applicable law prohibits a shorter
      limitations period.
    </p>
    <p>
      If you are a consumer in the EU, UK, or another jurisdiction whose
      law grants you a non-waivable right to bring a dispute in your
      home courts, this section does not override that right.
    </p>

    <h2>15. Entire agreement; assignment; no waiver</h2>
    <p>
      These terms, together with the
      <a href="/legal/privacy">privacy policy</a> and the
      <a href="/legal/refund">refund policy</a>, are the entire
      agreement between you and Wyreup regarding your use of the
      service. We may assign these terms to a successor in connection
      with a merger, acquisition, or sale of substantially all assets;
      you may not assign without our prior written consent. Our failure
      to enforce any provision is not a waiver of that or any other
      provision.
    </p>

    <h2>16. Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Questions about these terms: <strong>hello@wyreup.com</strong>.<br />
      Security disclosures: <strong>security@wyreup.com</strong>.
    </p>

    <p class="footnote">
      These terms are a working framework drafted in plain language for
      transparency. They are not a substitute for advice from a lawyer
      qualified in your jurisdiction. If you need a binding
      interpretation, consult counsel.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: var(--space-6) var(--space-4) var(--space-12);
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    color: var(--text-primary);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  .legal h1 {
    font-size: var(--text-2xl, 28px);
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-2);
  }
  .legal h2 {
    font-size: var(--text-md);
    margin: var(--space-6) 0 var(--space-2);
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }
  .legal p,
  .legal ul {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-3);
  }
  .legal ul {
    padding-left: var(--space-5);
  }
  .legal li {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }
  .legal code {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.92em;
    background: var(--bg-elevated);
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    padding: 1px 4px;
  }
  .meta {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    color: var(--text-subtle);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }
  .lede {
    font-style: italic;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--border-strong, currentColor);
    padding-left: var(--space-3);
    margin: var(--space-4) 0 var(--space-6);
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }
  .footnote {
    margin-top: var(--space-8);
    padding-top: var(--space-4);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border-soft, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08));
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    color: var(--text-subtle);
  }
</style>
